node.text:
#PressPlay: Get y’all popcorn ready, Chance the Rapper’s new movie drops today in theaters across the country! “Chance the Rapper’s Magnificent Coloring World” marks the first time an artist has independently distributed a film to theatres.
________
“Magnificent Coloring World” is a concert film self-distributed through Chance the Rapper’s House of Kicks production company and film house.
________
Chance wrote, produced, edited and starred in the film, working hard this past year to bring never-before-seen footage to his fans. The footage was filmed in 2017 right before Chance took home 3 Grammys for his critically acclaimed mixtape “Coloring Book.”
________
Fans will be able to see the film in person for a limited time in several cities including Los Angeles, New York, Chicago, Detori, Las Vegas and Philly.

node.title: Chance The Rapper’s Film Released Today

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Shade Room on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

Photo by The Shade Room on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'theshaderoom amberrose 3m Mibል TR SHADE ROOM I'm tired of being mentally and emotionally abused by people that love I've been suffering in silence for a long time and can't take it anymore. That's why I've been so quiet I've been a shell of who I used to be but refuse to let anyone damage me anymore.Family or not.'.

node.text:
TSR STAFF: Danielle J!
@prettyaries16
________________
#Roommates, #Amazon just continues to get to the bag—and this time the company managed to beat #Walmart in the process. According to @Forbes, for the very first time in the company’s history, #Amazon outsold the world’s largest retailer, Walmart. Within the last 12 months, Amazon racked up a jaw-dropping $610 billion in sales compared to Walmart’s $566 billion. 
________________
Amazon’s first place rank was largely due to the pandemic of 2020, when stay-at-home orders and quarantines forced people to buy their products online. This translated to Amazon’s sales increasing by $200 million from June 2020 to June 2021. 📸: (@gettyimages)
